FT  08 DEC 93 / Romania in IMF accord
The Romanian government yesterday said it had reached agreement with the
International Monetary Fund and expected to sign a letter of intent for a
new standby arrangement tomorrow, writes Virginia Marsh. The World Bank has
said it will disburse the second tranche of a 1992 structural adjustment
loan, worth Dollars 180m, as soon as the letter of intent is signed.
